ace of both awe and elegy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aAmerican poetry. 0aNaturevPoetry. 7aPOETRY / General.2bisacsh  apoems, united states, literature, fine arts, written word, prose, creativity, humanities, poetry collections, american writers, chicago, phoenix poets series, landscapes, vision, emotion, heartfelt, weight of history, supple, reflections, conscience, sensuousness, gravitas, irreverence, witty, engaging, existential questions, deprivation, pain, loss, sadness, grief, humanity, rumination.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z97831107109840 cprintz978022641745540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226417592423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226417592/original  a978-3-11-071098-4  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles